== Introduction == {{Infobox government agency |agency_name = Ministry of Justice of the Republic of Lithuania |type = [[Ministry (collective executive)|Ministry]] |nativename = Lietuvos Respublikos teisingumo ministerija |nativename_a = |nativename_r = |logo = |logo_width = |logo_caption = |seal = |seal_width = |seal_caption = |picture = Gedimino 30 a.JPG |picture_width = |picture_caption = |formed = <!-- {{Start date|YYYY|MM|DD}} --> |preceding1 = |preceding2 = <!-- (etc.) --> |dissolved = |superseding = |jurisdiction = |headquarters = [[Vilnius]], [[Lithuania]] |coordinates = |employees = |budget = |minister1_name = [[Elvinas Jankevičius]] |minister1_pfo = |minister2_name = |minister2_pfo = <!-- (etc.) --> |deputyminister1_name = |deputyminister1_pfo = |deputyminister2_name = |deputyminister2_pfo = <!-- (etc.) --> |chief1_name = |chief1_position = |chief2_name = |chief2_position = <!-- (etc.) --> |agency_type = |parent_department = |parent_agency = |child1_agency = |child2_agency = <!-- (etc.) --> |keydocument1= <!-- (etc.) --> |website = {{URL|www.tm.lt}} |footnotes = |map = |map_width = |map_caption = }}
The '''Ministry of Justice of the Republic of Lithuania''' ({{lang-lt|Lietuvos Respublikos teisingumo ministerija}}) was established in 1918. Its departments include European Law, prisons, state-guaranteed legal aid services in several major Lithuania cities, a [[patent]] bureau, [[consumer rights]] protection, the [[Law Institute of Lithuania|Law Institute]], the [[Metrology]] Inspectorate, state enterprise and legal information centers, and [[forensic science]].
