'''World Plaza'''<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://daiichiproperties.com/world-plaza/|title=World Plaza {{!}} Daiichi Properties|work=Daiichi Properties|access-date=2017-04-27|language=en-US}}</ref> is a 27-storey office building in [[Bonifacio Global City]] (BGC), Philippines. It is a development of Daiichi Properties with Gensler, the team who also developed the Best Office Development in the [[Philippines]] at the Asia Pacific Property Awards, [[One World Place]] in 2011. World Plaza is a Class A building and a [[PEZA]] registered IT Park.<ref>{{cite web|title=Daiichi Properties Helps Boost Philippines’ Real Estate Boom|url=http://www.gensleron.com/work/2013/10/30/daiichi-properties-helps-boost-philippines-real-estate-boom.html|website=www.gensleron.com/|accessdate=16 September 2014}}</ref> It has 18 floors of typical office space, penthouse level, and mechanical deck floor.
==Location== World Plaza is located along 5th Avenue in the Crescent West District. It is located adjacent to the upcoming [[ArthaLand Tower]] and close to the new [[Shangri-La Hotel]] in BGC.
==Design and features== World Plaza's architectural height is 115 m / 377&nbsp;ft and its height to tip is 115 m / 377&nbsp;ft.<ref>{{cite web|title=The Skyscraper Center: World Plaza|url=http://new.skyscrapercenter.com/pdf/world-plaza_2014-09-15-21-16-19.pdf|website=new.skyscrapercenter.com/}}</ref> Aiming to be LEED Gold-Certified, World Plaza offers sustainable and eco-friendly features. Unlike typical building lots, World Plaza's location is triangular, seemingly rotated in a 90-degree angle.{{citation needed|date=December 2015}}
